AGI - The exchange between four Israeli hostages who died would take place tomorrow during the imprisonment and the 620 Palestinian prisoners who were to return free last Saturday. Two sources of <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2025-02-25/con-gaza-distrutta-hamas-ammette-non-ci-sarebbe-state-attack-7-October-30171774/">Hamas.</a>
"The mediators informed Hamas that l<a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2025-02-25/hamas-agreement-release-prisoners-30184856/">o exchange will happen Thursday"</a>, said a group member, "Hamas and other resistance factions will return the bodies of four Israeli prisoners and in return Israel will release more Palestinian prisoners." &nbsp;The exchange, has clarified another source, "will happen simultaneously". >
&nbsp; The agreement was confirmed by the office of Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu.<br> The hope is that talks will be opened for the second phase of the ceasefire agreement.> US President Donald Trump's envoy, Steve Witkoff, appeared optimistic. "We are making a lot of progress," he said, "the negotiations will begin or in Doha or Cairo." &nbsp;

